.TH single 1M
.SH NAME
single \- switch the system to single-user mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\f3/etc/single\f1
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I single
switches the system to single-user mode and turns the
.IR getty s
off.
.I single
is a shell script that invokes
.IR /etc/telinit .
.SH SEE ALSO
getty(1M),
init(1M),
kill(1),
killall(1M),
multi(1M),
inittab(4).
